The developer used the `fuzzy-matcher` crate with `SkimMatcherV2` for fuzzy search. Here's a simplified implementation:
rust
use fuzzy_matcher::skim::SkimMatcherV2;

let matcher = SkimMatcherV2::default();
let scored: Vec<_> = items
    .iter()
    .filter_map(|item| {
        matcher.fuzzy_match(&item.name, query)
            .map(|score| (item, score))
    })
    .collect();
scored.sort_by(|a, b| b.1.cmp(&a.1)); // Sort by score (highest first)

This provides instantaneous, VSCode-like search results.

